&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a chance to develop your nursing skills in our local community hospital this winter?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Community Hospital nursing team is looking for registered nurses to join our friendly and supportive team based in Didcot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will demonstrate a passion for providing great rehabilitation care to our patients and have a highly motivated attitude with excellent communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you a rewarding working environment with clinical supervision and in-depth training where you will have the scope and ability to expand your core nursing skills. You will be part of a dedicated team of Nurses and Allied Health Professionals all working to thrive in making a difference to a patient’s recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team is part of an initiative “Creating with Care” project where we support our patients using therapeutic care with fun arts and crafts activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Didcot Community Hospital is located within South Oxfordshire, with great transport access to Oxford and Reading with local amenities on our doorstep.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Natalie Beal and Helen Reynolds, Ward Managers on 01865 904248.&lt;/p&gt;
